# Delivery conventions

Full guide: [Delivery conventions (issues, branches, commits, PRs)](https://linear.app/planogram/document/delivery-conventions-issues-branches-commits-prs-001627bba3a5).
Repo copy: `docs/LINEAR_ISSUE_TEMPLATE.md`.

Apply these formats whenever creating issues, branches, commits, or pull requests.

## Quick reference

| Action | Pattern | Example |
|--------|---------|---------|
| Issue title | Imperative phrase, ≤72 chars | `Manual shelf height resize (drag top border)` |
| Branch | `pla-<N>-<short-kebab-slug>` | `pla-15-manual-shelf-height-resize` |
| Commit | `<Summary>. (PLA-N).` | `Add shelf top-border drag handle. (PLA-15).` |
| PR title | `<Summary> (PLA-N).` | `Add shelf top-border drag handle (PLA-15).` |

## Linear issues

- Body sections: **Goal** → **Acceptance criteria** → **Out of scope** → **Links**
- Labels (one primary): `feature` | `bug` | `chore` | `debt`
- Status: Backlog → Todo → In Progress → In Review → Done
- PR-sized; create issue before planned work

## Branches

- Format: `pla-<N>-<short-kebab-slug>` from issue title (lowercase, hyphens)
- One branch per issue; never commit to `main`

## Commits

- `<Imperative summary>. (PLA-N).` — present tense, ≤72 chars before `(PLA-N)`
- Prefer a `chore` issue + `(PLA-N)` over omitting the reference

## Pull requests

- Title matches commit/PR pattern with `(PLA-N).` at end
- Body: `## Summary` + `## Test plan` + `PLA-N` line for GitHub↔Linear automation
- Target `main`; issue → In Review when PR opens, Done when merged
